.SH git\-adr\-new(1) \(en Create a new Architecture Decision Record
.SS SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]git adr new\f[R] TITLE OPTIONS
.SS DESCRIPTION
Create a new Architecture Decision Record with the given title.
By default, opens your configured editor with a template for the ADR
content.
The ADR is stored in git notes after editing.
.SS ARGUMENTS
.TP
\f[CR]TITLE\f[R]
The title for the new ADR.
Used to generate a unique ADR ID in the format
\f[CR]YYYYMMDD\-slug\-from\-title\f[R].
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-status\f[R] [proposed|accepted|deprecated|superseded|draft]
Initial status for the ADR (default: proposed).
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-tags\f[R], \f[CR]\-t\f[R] TEXT
Tags for categorization.
Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-link\f[R] TEXT
Commit SHA to link to this ADR.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-template\f[R] [madr|nygard|y\-statement]
Template format to use (overrides default).
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-file\f[R], \f[CR]\-f\f[R] PATH
Read ADR content from a file instead of opening editor.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-no\-edit\f[R]
Skip editor; requires \(enfile or stdin input.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-preview\f[R]
Show the template without creating an ADR.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-draft\f[R]
Mark as draft status (shortcut for \(enstatus draft).
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Show help message and exit.
.SS INPUT MODES
git\-adr\-new supports multiple input modes:
.TP
\f[B]Editor mode\f[R] (default)
Opens your configured editor ($EDITOR, $VISUAL, or fallback) with the
template.
Save and close to create the ADR.
.TP
\f[B]File input\f[R]
Use \f[CR]\-\-file path/to/content.md\f[R] to read from a file.
.TP
\f[B]Stdin input\f[R]
Pipe content: \f[CR]cat adr.md | git adr new \(dqTitle\(dq\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]Preview mode\f[R]
Use \f[CR]\-\-preview\f[R] to see the template without creating.
.SS TEMPLATES
The template includes standard sections based on the format:
.PP
\f[B]MADR (default)\f[R]: \- Context and Problem Statement \- Decision
Drivers \- Considered Options \- Decision Outcome \- Pros and Cons of
Options \- Consequences
.PP
\f[B]Nygard\f[R]: \- Status \- Context \- Decision \- Consequences
.PP
\f[B]y\-statement\f[R]: \- In the context of\&...
\- facing\&...
\- we decided\&...
\- to achieve\&...
\- accepting\&...
.SS EXAMPLES
Create an ADR with editor:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr new \(dqUse PostgreSQL for primary database\(dq
.EE
.PP
Create with specific status and tags:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr new \(dqAdopt React\(dq \-\-status accepted \-\-tags frontend \-\-tags ui
.EE
.PP
Create from file:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr new \(dqAPI Design\(dq \-\-file api\-decision.md
.EE
.PP
Create from stdin:
.IP
.EX
$ cat << \(aqEOF\(aq | git adr new \(dqUse REST API\(dq
## Context
We need an API design approach.

## Decision
Use RESTful API design.
EOF
.EE
.PP
Preview template:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr new \(dqExample\(dq \-\-preview \-\-template nygard
.EE
.PP
Link to commit during creation:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr new \(dqDatabase Migration\(dq \-\-link abc1234
.EE
